mrmc.gui

Class GUInterface

  • java.lang.Object
    • mrmc.gui.GUInterface

  • public class GUInterface
extends java.lang.Object
    This class describes the graphic interface. From top to bottom, the GUI includes
    1. Menu bar (References, About, Manual)
    2. Input Panel, which uses card layout and has 3 cards
        1) database as input
        2) pilot study or raw data input
        3) manual input components
    3. a label of AUC values, size of the study, etc.
    4. a table with all components of variance for the origianl study
    5. Sizing panel
    6. a table with all components of variance for the resulting study
    7. a label of statistical analysis resutls
    8. database summary panel

    Workflow possibilities are determined by selectedInput
    1. If selectedInput == "IMRMC" then reader study data is from .imrmc file:
    Click the Browse button (brwsButtonListener)
    • Resets GUI.
    • Browses for reader study .imrmc file with file chooser.
    • Creates InputFile object from .imrmc file
      ---- Object contains IDs for readers, cases, modalities ---- Object contains core data structures keyedData and truthVals
    Click the Variance Analysis Button (InputFileCard.varAnalysisListener)
    Author:
    Xin He, Ph.D,, Brandon D. Gallas, Ph.D, Rohan Pathare
